---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Our Mission | WM Smile Generation Uganda Limited">
    <main>
        <!-- Page Header Section -->
        <section class="relative h-64 flex items-center justify-center text-center text-white">
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-cover bg-center" style="background-image: url('/images/logo4.jpg');"></div>
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black opacity-60"></div>
            <div class="relative px-4">
                <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold">Our Mission in Action</h1>
                <p class="text-lg mt-2">How we're creating tangible change in education, nature, and wellbeing.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Mission 1: Education -->
        <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-white">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
                    <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                        <h3 class="text-green-800 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Pillar One</h3>
                        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-4">Fostering a Love for Learning</h2>
                        <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                            Education is the cornerstone of empowerment. At SMILE GENERATION UGANDA LIMITED, we go beyond traditional learning by reaching out village to village, focusing on areas where the need is greatest. We work closely with local communities to help educate their children by providing essential learning materials and ongoing educational support. Our programs focus on literacy, numeracy, and critical thinking skills to prepare children for a brighter future in environments where they feel supported and valued.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="text-lg text-stone-700 space-y-3 list-disc list-inside">
                            <li>Traveling directly to villages most in need to bring educational resources.</li>
                            <li>Helping community members to teach and support their childrenâ€™s learning.</li>
                            <li>Providing books, school supplies, and materials needed to study.</li>
                            <li>Offering continuous educational assistance to ensure children stay engaged and supported.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <img src="images/school.jfif" alt="Children reading books outdoors" class="rounded-lg shadow-2xl w-full">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Mission 2: Nature Awareness -->
        <section class="py-20 md:py-28 brownish-gradient">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
                    <div class="order-2 md:order-1">
                        <img src="images/enviroment_mission.jpeg" alt="Community members planting trees" class="rounded-lg shadow-2xl w-full">
                    </div>
                    <div class="order-1 md:order-2 text-center md:text-left">
                        <h3 class="text-green-800 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Pillar Two</h3>
                        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-4">Cultivating Environmental Stewards</h2>
                        <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                            We believe that a healthy planet is essential for a healthy community. Our nature awareness efforts help instill a sense of responsibility and wonder for the environment in Uganda's youth. By actively participating in conservation, children learn valuable lessons about sustainability and their role in protecting our shared home.
                        </p>
                         <ul class="text-lg text-stone-700 space-y-3 list-disc list-inside">
                            <li>Community tree planting drives for reforestation.</li>
                            <li>Outdoor activities and nature exploration to foster environmental appreciation.</li>
                            <li>Workshops on waste reduction and recycling.</li>
                            <li>Educational nature walks and biodiversity projects that connect children with their natural surroundings.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 mt-6 leading-relaxed">
                            This hands-on approach empowers children to become stewards of the environment, building a stronger future for their communities and the planet.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Mission 3: Protecting Refugee Children -->
        <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-white">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
                    <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                        <h3 class="text-green-800 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Pillar Three</h3>
                        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-4">Protecting Refugee Children</h2>
                        <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                           We recognize that children in refugee situations face immense hardships beyond education alone. We are dedicated to providing essential support that helps these children live with dignity and safety.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="text-lg text-stone-700 space-y-3 list-disc list-inside">
                            <li>Supplying blankets, beds, and basic non-perishable food items to improve living conditions.</li>
                            <li>Delivering essential materials that foster a stable and caring environment for learning and growth.</li>
                            <li>Offering continuous support to refugee families and children to meet daily needs.</li>
                            <li>Strengthening community resilience by ensuring children have the necessities to thrive despite displacement.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 mt-6 leading-relaxed">
                            Through practical aid and compassionate care, we aim to protect and uplift refugee children, helping them build hope and resilience for the future.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <img src="images/children_support.jpeg" alt="Support for refugee children" class="rounded-lg shadow-2xl w-full">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Impact Section -->
        <section class="bg-green-700">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-16 text-center text-white">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-12">Our Impact at a Glance</h2>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <div>
                        <p class="text-5xl font-bold">100</p>
                        <p class="text-xl mt-2 font-semibold">Children Protected</p>
                        <p class="mt-2">Provided with safe shelter, blankets, and food in crisis situations.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="text-5xl font-bold">2,500+</p>
                        <p class="text-xl mt-2 font-semibold">Learning Materials Distributed</p>
                        <p class="mt-2">Books, notebooks, and supplies delivered directly to rural and refugee communities.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="text-5xl font-bold">300+</p>
                        <p class="text-xl mt-2 font-semibold">Local Families Supported</p>
                        <p class="mt-2">Benefited from emergency aid, food packages, and educational tools.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
    <style>
        .brownish-gradient {
            background: linear-gradient(180deg, #FDFBF8 0%, #F5EFE6 100%);
        }
    </style>
</BaseLayout>
